221 East 73rd Street, north side, between Second and Third Avenues. This picture was taken during a fire in which about

About 1905.

Gift of Gustav Scholer.

707916f-a.text:
Second Ave., east side, north from East 73rd Street, showing pushcart and general household wares displayed on the sidewalk. This area is a thriving market place, used by the people of this district.

December 28, 1936.

P.L. Sperr.
